      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FEDERAL SENOR (8) was well backed last start but ran below expectations when fourth (23.19), beaten 8 lengths. Finished second the start before. Won at his only start from this draw. Can atone. SILENT MINUTE (1) stalked the lead from a low draw and fought on well to finish 2.75 lengths back in third (22.23) at this track in a NG over 388m. Ran one of the fastest times on the program last start despite finishing in the minors. Hard to beat again. NOVA LASS (2) last start finished 3rd over 388m at this track beaten 5.5 lengths (22.80) behind Laurie's Rupee in a Grade 5 on May 5. Looks well placed here and among the chances.",
